cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image classification using a novel optical neural network framework. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new approach to neural networks, which involves multiple levels of varying zoom, and thus it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and Siamese networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the use of optical technology, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
